Blekinge

The region of Blekinge within Sweden

Coat of arms of Blekinge

CountrySweden Number of zones831Maximum PPH1 109Last updated2023-04-11

Blekinge is one of 21 regions in Sweden. The region corresponds to Blekinge County in the south of Sweden.

It borders on the counties of Skåne in the west, Kronoberg and Kalmar in the north and the Baltic Sea in south and east.

The capital is Karlskrona.

It is the smallest of the present administrative counties of Sweden, covering only 0.7% of the total area.

Geographical overview[edit]

Municipalities[edit]

Blekinge consists of five municipalities:

Municipality Zones Karlshamn 153 Karlskrona 300 Olofström 98 Ronneby 172 Sölvesborg 108

The list is updated according to the zones that existed on 2023-04-11.

Zones[edit]

There are 831 turf zones in the region of Blekinge, of which one is counted as a world heritage site, nine water zones, seven train station zones, eight monument zones, 38 holy zones, one summit zone, 53 bridge zones, three castle zones and 11 ruin zones.
